parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause a fire, which can lead to vehicle damage, injury, or even death.
symptoms: Smoke or fire coming from the ignition switch
burning smell or smoke in the vehicle
sparks coming from the rear of the vehicle
loud noise followed by fire in the engine compartment.

symptoms: Smoke or fire coming from under the hood
sparks coming from the rear of the vehicle
loud noise followed by fire in the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a fire, which can lead to vehicle damage, injury, or even death.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine fires can cause significant damage to the vehicle, pose a risk to the occupants, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
Engine stalling and performance issues can cause inconvenience, loss of power, and potentially lead to accidents or strand the driver.
Engine component failures can cause engine damage, lead to costly repairs, and potentially cause accidents or strand the driver.
